      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void setup()
      Runs before every test, creates the BuyRoboticonsMarket object that is being tested and all other required objects
      void TestClickCompletePurchaseButtonFiveRoboticons()
      Ensures that when the transaction quantity spinbox is set to 5 and the complete purchase button clicked the player has 5 roboticons added to their inventory (assuming the player has enough money)
      void TestClickCompletePurchaseButtonFiveRoboticonsMarket()
      Ensures that when the transaction quantity spinbox is set to 5 and the complete purchase button clicked the market has 5 roboticons taken from its inventory
      void TestClickCompletePurchaseButtonFiveRoboticonsMoney()
      Ensures that when the transaction quantity spinbox is set to 5 and the complete purchase button clicked the player has the correct amount of money taken from their inventory (assuming the player has enough money)
      void TestClickCompletePurchaseButtonOneRoboticon()
      Ensures that when the transaction quantity spinbox is set to 1 and the complete purchase button clicked the player has 1 roboticon added to their inventory (assuming the player has enough money)
      void TestClickCompletePurchaseButtonOneRoboticonMarket()
      Ensures that when the transaction quantity spinbox is set to 1 and the complete purchase button clicked the market has 1 roboticon taken from its inventory
      void TestClickCompletePurchaseButtonOneRoboticonMoney()
      Ensures that when the transaction quantity spinbox is set to 1 and the complete purchase button clicked the player has the correct amount of money taken from their inventory (assuming the player has enough money)
      void TestClickCompletePurchaseButtonZeroRoboticonsMarket()
      Ensures that when the transaction quantity spinbox is set to 5 and the complete purchase button clicked the market has no roboticons taken from its inventory
      void TestClickCompletePurchaseButtonZeroRoboticonsMoney()
      Ensures that when the transaction quantity spinbox is set to 0 and the complete purchase button clicked the player has no money taken from their inventory
      void TestClickCompletePurchaseButtonZerosRoboticon()
      Ensures that when the transaction quantity spinbox is set to 0 and the complete purchase button clicked the player has 0 roboticons added to their inventory
      void TestClickCompletePurchaseNoPopUp()
      Ensures that when the players purchase does not fail that a MessagePopUp is not created.
      void TestClickCompletePurchaseNotEneoughMoney()
      Ensures that when the players purchase fails because the player does not have enough money that a MessagePopUp is created to alert the user to this.
      void TestProduceRoboticonButton()
      Ensures that when the produce roboticon button is clicked and the market has enough ore a roboticon is produced
      void TestProduceRoboticonButtonFailNotOreQuantity()
      Ensures that when the produce roboticon button is clicked and the market does not have enough ore its ore quantity is not changed
      void TestProduceRoboticonButtonFailNotProduced()
      Ensures that when the produce roboticon button is clicked and the market does not have enough ore a roboticon is not produced
      void TestProduceRoboticonButtonOreQuantity()
      Ensures that when the produce roboticon button is clicked and the market has enough ore the markets ore is reduced by the correct amount
      void TestProduceRoboticonFail()
      Ensures that when the produce roboticon button is clicked and that market fails to produce a roboticon (because it does not have enough ore) that a MesagePopUp is created to alert the user to this.
      void TestProduceRoboticonNoPopUp()
      Ensures that when the market does not fail to produce a roboticon a MessagePopUp is not created
